{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="saydo-intro">
  <p class="saydo-headline">
    One synthetic manager letter ({{ card_data.meta.manager_name }}), three stated
    views, read against the measured book. Two views match the positioning; one contradicts
    it &mdash; shown side by side, quote and measurement together, so the reader can inspect
    the conclusion.
  </p>
  <p class="saydo-headline">
    <strong>A language model is a system that turns prose into structured fields.</strong>
    Here it identifies the stated direction, theme, horizon, and exact quote. Deterministic
    code &mdash; ordinary fixed rules &mdash; compares those fields with the measured exposure.
  </p>
  <button type="button" class="saydo-focus" data-saydo-focus>Focus the contradiction</button>
</section>

<section class="saydo" data-saydo>
  {% for v in card_data.views %}
  <article class="saydo-row saydo-row--{{ v.label }}"
           data-instrument="{{ v.instrument }}"
           data-label="{{ v.label }}">
    <div class="saydo-side saydo-side--said">
      <span class="saydo-side__label">Said &middot; {{ v.letter_date }}</span>
      <blockquote class="saydo-quote">{{ v.quote }}</blockquote>
      <dl class="saydo-view">
        <dt>Direction</dt><dd>{{ v.direction }}</dd>
        <dt>Theme</dt><dd>{{ v.theme }}</dd>
        <dt>Conviction</dt>
        <dd class="saydo-conviction" aria-label="conviction {{ v.conviction }} of 3">
          {% for i in range(3) %}<span class="conviction-dot{% if i < v.conviction %} conviction-dot--on{% endif %}"></span>{% endfor %}
        </dd>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <div class="saydo-side saydo-side--did">
      <span class="saydo-side__label">Did &middot; {{ card_data.meta.horizon_months }}-month horizon</span>
      <div class="saydo-exposure"
           data-instrument="{{ v.instrument }}"
           data-start="{{ v.measured.start }}"
           data-end="{{ v.measured.end }}"
           data-delta="{{ v.measured.delta }}">
        <svg class="saydo-spark" viewBox="0 0 100 40" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true"></svg>
      </div>
      <dl class="saydo-measure">
        <dt>{{ v.instrument }}</dt>
        <dd>{{ "%+.3f"|format(v.measured.start) }} &rarr; {{ "%+.3f"|format(v.measured.end) }}
            (move {{ "%+.3f"|format(v.measured.move) }})</dd>
        <dt>Dead-band &delta;</dt>
        <dd>&plusmn;{{ "%.2f"|format(v.measured.delta) }}
            <span class="saydo-illustrative">illustrative, uncalibrated</span></dd>
      </dl>
      <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="{{ v.label }}">{{ v.label }}</span>
    </div>
  </article>
  {% endfor %}
</section>

<section class="saydo-intro" aria-labelledby="m5-exhibit-shows">
  <h2 id="m5-exhibit-shows" class="saydo-headline"><strong>What this exhibit shows</strong></h2>
  <p class="saydo-headline">
    <strong>What you are looking at.</strong> Three views pulled from one
    {{ card_data.meta.manager_name }} letter, each read against the manager's
    measured book over a {{ card_data.meta.horizon_months }}-month horizon. Two
    match: the value tilt rose {{ "%+.3f"|format(card_data.views[1].measured.move) }}
    and the net held flat at {{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.views[0].measured.end) }}.
    One contradicts: after saying it was trimming momentum, the book's momentum
    beta rose {{ "%+.3f"|format(card_data.views[2].measured.move) }} &mdash; against
    the stated direction, and more than twice the
    &plusmn;{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.views[2].measured.delta) }} dead-band.
  </p>
  <div class="saydo-honesty" role="note">
    <strong>How to read it.</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Each <strong>row</strong> is one stated view: the quote and direction on
        the &ldquo;Said&rdquo; side, the measured exposure path on the &ldquo;Did&rdquo; side.</li>
      <li>The <strong>sparkline</strong> is the exposure over the horizon;
        <strong>start &rarr; end (move)</strong> is what the fixed scoring rule reads.</li>
      <li>The <strong>dead-band &delta;</strong> is the materiality threshold &mdash; a
        move smaller than &delta; is noise, not a statement. Here it is
        illustrative and uncalibrated.</li>
      <li>The <strong>verdict chip</strong> is <em>aligned</em>, <em>partial</em>, or
        <em>contradicted</em>. The label comes from deterministic code, not the language model.</li>
      <li>Read the <a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/{{ card.id }}.html">technical
        method and provenance</a> for the equations and evaluation design.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <aside class="saydo-honesty" role="note">
    <strong>Evidence requirement.</strong> The extraction is illustrative. Real-letter output
    requires at least 80% precision and 80% recall for the core extracted fields, plus at
    least 80% alignment-label accuracy on independently checked examples.
  </aside>
</section>

<p class="saydo-footnote">
  &ldquo;Communication drift worth a conversation,&rdquo; never &ldquo;caught you.&rdquo;
  Every row shows the verbatim quote and measured series side by side. The dead-band
  &delta; remains illustrative and uncalibrated here; live use must calibrate it so ordinary
  noise rarely creates a false contradiction.
</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>A language model is a system that turns prose into structured fields. It reads the letter
and emits direction, theme, instrument, conviction, and exact quote. Deterministic code then
scores that view against the measured exposure path; the model never chooses the label.</p>
<p>A view is <em>aligned</em> when the exposure moves in the stated direction by
at least the dead-band &delta; over the horizon, <em>contradicted</em> when it
moves against the stated direction by at least &delta;, and <em>partial</em> when
the move stays inside the dead-band. A stated-flat view is <em>aligned</em> only while
the exposure stays inside &plusmn;&delta;. The demonstration threshold is illustrative;
live use must calibrate it on ordinary noisy paths.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/m5-saydo.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
